label: Reading Proficiency by Socio-Economic Status
note: The dataset uses rescaled indices of economic, social, and cultural status (ESCS) for trend analysis provided by the OECD: those of the years 2000, 2003, 2006, and 2009 have been harmonized to 2015, those of 2012, 2015 and 2018 to 2022.
source: Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), Program for International Student Assessment (PISA), 2000, 2003, 2006, 2009, 2012, 2015, 2018, and 2022 Reading and Mathematics Assessments.

definition.L1A: Readers at Level 1a can understand the literal meaning of sentences or short passages.
definition.L2: Readers at Level 2 can identify the main idea in a piece of text of moderate length.
definition.L3: Readers at Level 3 can represent the literal meaning of single or multiple texts in the absence of explicit content.
definition.L4: At Level 4, readers can comprehend extended passages in single or multiple-text settings.
definition.L5: Readers at Level 5 can comprehend lengthy texts, inferring which information in the text is relevant.
definition.L6: Readers at Level 6 can comprehend lengthy and abstract texts, integrating multiple perspectives.

definition.RS: Reading performance, for PISA, measures the capacity to understand, use and reflect on written texts in order to achieve goals, develop knowledge and potential, and participate in society. Scores are reported on a scale from 0 to 1000, the mean across OECD countries is set at 500 and the standard deviation at 100.
definition.FD: A specification of the way in which the frequencies of members of a population are distributed according to the values of the variates which they exhibit. For observed data, the distribution is usually specified in tabular form, with some grouping for continuous variates.
